2.5 Implementation and open source availability All molecular simulations were performed using the open source OpenMM 7.0 simulation package available for free download from http://openmm.org86,88.

All articial neural net- work construction and training was conducted using the Keras deep learning Python API available from https://github.com/fchollet/keras and running on top of the Theano libraries133.
The ANNForce biasing force plugin to OpenMM is available from https://github.com/weiHelloWorld/ANN_Force .

We have largely auto- mated the MESA framework to require minimal user intervention, and made it freely avail- able for public download ( https://github.com/weiHelloWorld/accelerated_sampling_ with_autoencoder ) together with a plugin implementing the biasing forces within the OpenMM simulation package86,88(https://github.com/weiHelloWorld/ANN_Force ).
Boxplots were generated using the seaborn Python libraries (https://seaborn.pydata.org ).
